```python
#queeries of city ==
#find mean of fare
average_fare_by_city = ride_data_df.groupby(['city'])['fare'].mean().reset_index()
#count of ride_id
count_ride_id = ride_data_df.groupby(['city'])['ride_id'].count().reset_index()
combined_ride_fare = pd.merge(average_fare_by_city, count_ride_id, how='left', on = 'city')
combined_data = pd.merge(combined_ride_fare, city_data_df, how='left', on = 'city')
#combined_data.rename(columns={'city':'City','fare': 'Average Fare','ride_id': 'Ride Count','driver_count':'Driver Count','type':'Type'})
combined_data.head(5)
```

```python
# create data
colors = {'Urban':'gold','Suburban':'lightskyblue','Rural':'lightcoral'}
combined_data['color'] = combined_data['type'].apply(lambda x: colors[x])

combined_data.plot.scatter(x='ride_id', y='fare', c=combined_data['color'], s=combined_data['driver_count']*5);
plt.xlabel("Average Fare (5)")
plt.ylabel("Total Number of Rides (Per City)")
plt.title("Pyber Ride Sharing Data (2016)")
plt.legend()
plt.tight_layout()

```

```python
P = combined_data.groupby('type')['fare'].sum().reset_index()
P['Percentage'] = 100 * P['fare']  / P['fare'].sum()
fare_types = P['type'] 
fare_percentages = P['Percentage']
P.plot(kind='pie', y = 'Percentage', colors=combined_data['color'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, shadow=False, labels=P['type'], legend = True, fontsize=14)
```
